(6477, 4264, 'main_template_text_column_1', '<h2>AUTISM</h2>\r\n<h3>ASD (Autism Spectrum Disorder)</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Autism is a range of development disorder characterised by difficulties in socialisation and communication and\r\nrestricted/ repetitive pattern of behaviour and interest.</li>\r\n 	<li>Autism appears to have it’s roots in very early brain development and the most obvious signs and symptoms of\r\nautism emerge between 2 and 3 years of age.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\r\n<ul>Examples of ASD:</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Autism</li>\r\n 	<li>Childhood disintegrative Disorder (CDD)</li>\r\n 	<li>Aspergers Syndrome</li>\r\n 	<li>Pervasive Development Disorder – Non Otherwise Specified (PDD-NOS)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>'),
